<HEADLINE>
<P>
DOWNTIME: BODY WATCH; TUNING IN TO THE TURTLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 On warm, sunny Sunday afternoons when the sun isn't too hot, I like to drag my 
huge papasan chair out in my back yard and read the paper or a good book.My 
neighbors have a turtle about the size of a puppy. While I'm reading, the 
turtle will do laps around my chair. When I want to take a break from reading, 
I'll count how many seconds it takes the turtle to complete a full circle. It's 
very relaxing watching the turtle haul its heavy shell. 
</P>
<P>
 -- CASSI GLISPER 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
