<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRO FOOTBALL DAILY REPORT; RAMS; NO. 2 RECEIVER SPOT STILL TO BE FILLED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By T.J. SIMERS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Rams' ongoing auditions for a receiver to play opposite starter Flipper 
Anderson have been interrupted by injuries. 
</P>
<P>
 Rookie Chris Brantley, who had caught the attention of the coaching staff, has 
been sidelined because of a hamstring injury. 
</P>
<P>
 "Brantley has been very impressive," Coach Chuck Knox said. "I just hope this 
is a temporary setback." 
</P>
<P>
 Monday, on the final play of practice, wide receiver Sean LaChapelle was 
tackled by Dexter Davis in a non-tackling drill and injured his leg. 
</P>
<P>
 The Rams began training camp with 11 wide receivers competing for three or 
four spots. Jeff Jones was released earlier this week, and Todd Kinchen was 
placed on the injured list because of a knee injury. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Defensive end Robert Young had seven sacks in the first four games last 
season, then injured a knee and was lost for the year. 
</P>
<P>
 Now, he's back, and according to Knox, is in prime form. 
</P>
<P>
 "He has looked great and has dominated in the one-on-one pass rushes," Knox 
said. T.J. SIMERS 
</P>
