<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASEBALL DAILY REPORT; ANGELS; RODGERS HIRED AS SCOUT BY PHILLIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ELLIOTT TEAFORD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Former Manager Buck Rodgers, fired by the Angels on May 17, has been hired by 
the Philadelphia Phillies as their major league scout on the West Coast. 
</P>
<P>
 Philadelphia General Manager Lee Thomas and Manager Jim Fregosi were Rodgers' 
teammates on the Angels in the 1960s. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 A decision on the site of the Angel-Seattle Mariner series Aug. 2-4 is 
expected to be made today or Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 King County officials will determine whether 40,000 damaged ceiling tiles can 
be removed in time to play the three-game series at Seattle's Kingdome, as 
scheduled. If the 59,166-seat stadium is unavailable, the series probably will 
be shifted to Cheney Stadium in Tacoma, home of the Oakland Athletics' triple-A 
affiliate; B.C. Place in Vancouver, Canada, or Anaheim Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 The Mariners, who have been forced to postpone two games with the Baltimore 
Orioles and shift three home games with the Red Sox to Boston's Fenway Park, 
had no further comment Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Angel third base coach Ken Macha became manager of the Tempe Rafters of the 
Arizona Fall League on Monday. The Rafters, whose roster will include top 
prospects from the Angels, Dodgers, Texas Rangers, St. Louis Cardinals and 
Detroit Tigers, won the league's championship last season. ELLIOTT TEAFORD 
</P>
