<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP EXECUTIVE HIRED BY THE KINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Lester Wintz, an executive for World Cup '94, has become executive vice 
president of the Kings. 
</P>
<P>
 Wintz, who was a senior vice president and chief of external affairs for World 
Cup '94 the past two years, will be in charge of business operations for the 
Kings, the club said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Before his World Cup stint, Wintz was a senior vice president for marketing 
with Great Western Financial Corp. 
</P>
