</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police Monday asked for help in finding the hit-and-run driver whose car 
fatally injured a 5-year-old boy crossing a street in the Westlake area to get 
ice cream. 
</P>
<P>
 Armando Davila was struck about 2:30 p.m. Saturday at Westlake Avenue and 11th 
Place, said Los Angeles Police Detective Sonia Cabrera of the Central Traffic 
Division. The car, which sped southbound on Westlake Avenue, may have been a 
taxi, Cabrera said. 
