</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Machine Tool Orders Up 17.4% in June: Orders also jumped 20% for the first 
half of 1994 from the same period a year ago, an industry trade group said. The 
Assn. for Manufacturing Technology announced that June orders for U.S.-made 
machine tools totaled $379.2 million, compared to $322.9 million in May and 
$313.7 million in June, 1993.Orders for the first six months of 1994 totaled 
$2.12 billion, an increase from $1.77 billion for the first half of 1993, the 
group said. "Late last year, most forecasters were predicting a relatively flat 
order rate for the first six months of '94," said Albert W. Moore, president of 
the McLean, Va.-based association. "In light of this, the 20% increase 
year-on-year through June is welcome news." 
</P>
