<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: AIRLINES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 USAir Pilots Prepare an Offer: The union representing the pilots said it will 
offer the struggling carrier $750 million in wage concessions in return for 
part ownership.The cuts would be spread over five years, with the pilots 
contributing about a third of the $500 million in annual savings USAir is 
seeking from employees. The Air Line Pilots Assn. said its offer is contingent 
on a financial restructuring of USAir that would include the infusion of new 
operating funds. British Airways has halted new investments in the airline 
until it works out new deals with its employees. 
</P>
