<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: HUNTINGTON BEACH; SEARCH UNDERWAY FOR DEPUTY CITY ATTORNEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DEBRA CANO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A new deputy city attorney will be hired to handle personal injury and 
personnel grievance cases in an effort to save the city money on outside 
attorney costs. 
</P>
<P>
 City Atty.Gail Hutton said a deputy will be hired at a cost of nearly $66,000 
a year. 
</P>
<P>
 Hutton said the money to pay the salary and benefits for the new employee will 
not come from the general-fund budget but from a separate risk-management fund. 
</P>
<P>
 Hutton said that the average cost for an outside attorney to defend the city 
in a grievance case is about $12,450, compared to about $4,000 for an attorney 
working on the city payroll.  
</P>
<P>
 From January, 1993, to March this year, 25 of 44 cases have been handled by 
deputy city attorneys and temporary attorney employees at an estimated cost 
savings of $311,250, Hutton said. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition, Hutton said that the city's risk-management budget for hiring 
outside legal counsel for injury and grievance cases has been exceeded in the 
past two fiscal years. 
</P>
<P>
 Hutton said that the 1993-94 budget is $400,000 for outside counsel. 
</P>
<P>
 But costs to date for these cases exceed $1 million, primarily due to two 
"very risky cases" that were costly, she said. 
</P>
<P>
 Hutton said recruitment is underway to hire the attorney after the City 
Council approved the position. 
</P>
<P>
 Hutton also said over the past few years her office has significantly reduced 
its staffing due to budget constraints. 
</P>
<P>
 As a result, she said, her department has not had enough attorneys to handle 
the case load. 
</P>
<P>
 The office currently has seven attorneys. DEBRA CANO 
</P>
</TEXT>
