ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: VILLA PARK; COUPLE DISPLACED BY FIRE IN HOME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KEN ELLINGWOOD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two people were displaced Monday after an attic fire that injured two 
firefighters the day before. 
</P>
<P>
 The fire, believed sparked by an electrical problem, caused an estimated 
$400,000 in damage to a two-story house in the 18000 block of James Road, said 
Orange County Fire Department spokeswoman Maria Sabol. 
</P>
<P>
 An Orange city firefighter suffered a neck injury from debris falling from the 
roof and attic, and a county firefighter suffered a scratch on the eye, Sabol 
said. Both were treated and released from local hospitals. 
</P>
<P>
 The fire, reported at 2:44 p.m. Sunday, was under control 40 minutes later. 
</P>
<P>
 The couple living in the home were inside at the time of the fire but unaware 
of it until neighbors spotted smoke, Sabol said. KEN ELLINGWOOD 
