Street when a car pulled up about 1:50 a.m., police said. When the teen-ager 
approached the car to talk to the driver, shots were fired from the passenger 
window, hitting all three victims. Figueroa was later pronounced dead at 
Fountain Valley Regional Hospital and Medical Center. 
