<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN HELD IN SHOOTING OF CHILD PLEADS NOT GUILTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ANN W. O'NEILL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man accused of wounding a 3-year-old girl while shooting at her mother 
pleaded not guilty Monday to attempted murder charges.  
</P>
<P>
 Juan Manolo Cienfuegos, 24, of Tujunga faces a preliminary hearing in Van Nuys 
Municipal Court on Aug. 3.He is being held in County Jail on $2.1 million bail. 
</P>
<P>
 Injuries received by the child, Vanessa Barcenas, were not life-threatening, 
and she is recovering, police said. She was shot Thursday afternoon outside the 
Saticoy Plaza apartment complex in Reseda. Police said the apparent motive was 
an ongoing dispute between the child's mother, Eileen Cortez, 21, and 
Cienfuegos' former girlfriend, Christina Stevens, also 21. 
</P>
<P>
 Cienfuegos apparently was helping Stevens move furniture out of her former 
apartment when the dispute escalated. Police said Ciefuegos fired five or six 
shots into a group of people outside the complex in the 17800 block of Saticoy 
Street. 
</P>
<P>
 Cienfuegos has been charged with four counts of attempted murder and a single 
charge of causing great bodily injury. ANN W. O'NEILL 
</P>
