<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: REXON REPORTS NET INCOME OF $220,000 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rexon Inc., a Simi Valley supplier of computer software and data storage 
products, reported a profit turnaround in its fiscal third quarter from a 
year-earlier loss. 
</P>
<P>
 In the three months that ended July 3, Rexon had net income of $220,000, in 
contrast with a net loss of $48.2 million a year before.Its net sales rose 16% 
in the recent quarter, to $53.1 million from $45.7 million. 
</P>
<P>
 For the nine months, the company reported earnings of $258,000, while its net 
sales increased 6%, to $152.8 million. In the same period a year ago, it had a 
loss of $46.8 million on $143.9 million in sales. 
</P>
<P>
 Rexon attributed the improved results to its continuing cost-reduction 
program, the development of new multimedia products, expansion of its software 
business and its new Singapore manufacturing operation. 
</P>
